94":"11 August 1194","1196":"1196","1141":"1141","1195":"1195","1194":"1194","1182":"1182","1180":"1180","UM 1160":"about 1160","NACH 1236":"after 1236","1236":"1236","1168":"1168","1135":"1135","12 Nov 1195":"12 November 1195","about 1220":"1220","ABT 1180":"about 1180","ABT 1182":"about 1182","1218":"1218","Grenzau, Rheinland-Pfalz, Germany":"Grenzau, Höhr-Grenzhausen, Westerwaldkreis, Rhineland-Palatinate, Germany","of,Morle,Hessen-Nassau,Prussia":"Hesse-Nassau, Prussia, Germany","nameMeanings":[{"name":"von","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Altered form of Welsh   Vaughan  .","Chinese: variant of   Wong  .","Cambodian: written វ៉ុន, unexplained."],"variants":[{"name":"Vaughan","meanings":["Welsh: from <i>fychan</i>, a lenited form of <i>bychan</i>, a diminutive of <i>bach</i> ‘little’. This was often used to distinguish the younger of two bearers of the same personal name, typically the son of a father with the same name."]}]},{"name":"Staden","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of Family Names in Britain and Ireland © University of the West of England 2016","meanings":["1  English: locative name from Staden in King Sterndale (Derbys).","2  English:  see  Staddon  ."],"variants":[{"name":"Staton","meanings":["English:","habitational name from Stathern (Leicestershire), from Old English <i>staca</i> ‘stake’ + <i>thyrne</i> ‘thorn bush’.","variant of <b>Staden</b>, a habitational name from Staden in King Sterndale (Derbyshire), from Old English <i>stæf</i> ‘staff, stave, rod’ + <i>dūn</i> ‘hill’."]},{"name":"Staddon","meanings":["English: habitational name from any of the six minor places in Devon called Staddon, in Hartland, Holsworthy, Broadwoodwidger, Plymstock, North Tawton, and Cheriton Bishop parishes, or from Staddon in Winsford (Somerset). The placename derives from Old English <i>stōd</i> ‘stud, herd of horses’ or <i>stot</i> ‘horse, bullock’ + <i>dūn</i> ‘hill’."]},{"name":"Statton","meanings":["English: probably a variant of <b>Staden</b> (see   Staton   2) or   Staddon  ."]}]},{"name":"Euphemia","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["form of a Late Greek name derived from <i>eu</i> ‘well, good’ + <i>phēnai</i> ‘to speak’. This was the name of various early saints, notably a virgin martyr said to have been burned at the stake at Chalcedon in  307 . It had a limited popularity in some regions in the 16th and 17th centuries and returned to favour in the Victorian period, especially in the pet form   Effie .  It is little used at present."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"When Euphemia von Staden was born in 1168, her father, Graf Konrad von Peilstein II, was 34 and her mother, Sophia von Vohburg, was 28. She had at least 2 sons and 1 daughter with Siegfried II von Büdingen, Graf von Mörle und Kleeberg. She died in 1236, at the age of 68."},"et":{"1168–1236":"1168–1236","1164–1194":"1164–1194","1180–1196":"1180–1196","1182–1218":"1182–1218","1190–1220":"1190–1220","1135–1195":"1135–1195","1141–1176":"1141–1176","1190":"1190","about 1190":"1190","12 Mar 1176":"12. märts 1176","1176":"1176","1220":"1220","1164":"1164","11 AUG 1194":"11. august 1194","1196":"1196","1141":"1141","1195":"1195","1194":"1194","1182":"1182","1180":"1180","UM 1160":"umbes 1160","NACH 1236":"pärast 1236","1236":"1236","1168":"1168","1135":"1135","12 Nov 1195":"12. november 1195","about 1220":"1220","ABT 1180":"umbes 1180","ABT 1182":"umbes 1182","1218":"1218","Grenzau, Rheinland-Pfalz, Germany":"Grenzau, Höhr-Grenzhausen, Westerwaldkreis, Rheinland-Pfalz, Saksamaa","of,Morle,Hessen-Nassau,Prussia":"Hessen-Nassau, Preußen, Saksamaa"},"fi":{"1168–1236":"1168–1236","1164–1194":"1164–1194","1180–1196":"1180–1196","1182–1218":"1182–1218","1190–1220":"1190–1220","1135–1195":"1135–1195","1141–1176":"1141–1176","1190":"1190","about 1190":"1190","12 Mar 1176":"12. maaliskuuta 1176","1176":"1176"